nodes.text: Mean while, California, is outlawing mail order ammunition purchases, allowing only 50 rounds at any one sale, and requiring a finger print at point of sale.

Oh yeah, like that hasn't been tried before /sarcasm It darn sure isn't about crime control. No doubt some nefarious excuse to farther control the people and attempt to charge user fees to discourage a right. No doubt sinjin will approve so 'they' can match fingerprints and type of ammo to the DROS registration file?
